  "title": "Effects of spiral testing and review on retention and mathematical achievement for below‐average eighth‐ and ninth‐grade students",
  "abstract": "Two groups of below average eighth graders and ninth graders were tested using a traditional testing scheme and a spiral testing scheme. The ninth graders who were tested using the spiral approach scored significantly higher than the control group in a pre‐algebra class on both a mid‐semester test as well as a semester test. The eighth graders who were tested using the spiral approach scored significantly higher than the control group in a basic mathematics course on a mid‐semester test.",
